HostRange(3)          User Contributed Perl Documentation         HostRange(3)



NNaammee
       HostRange.pm

UUssaaggee
       use HostRange; my @hosts = HostRange::parse
       'foo-[ab][05,09-12].bar.com'

PPaatttteerrnnss
       Simple atoms of one character:

         HostRange::parse 'foo-[a-c]'          # ["foo-a", "foo-b", "foo-c"]

       Ranges are parsed using the perl aXX..aXX operator:

         HostRange::parse 'foo-[a-c]'          # ["foo-a", "foo-b", "foo-c"]

       Multiple atoms and ranges separated by commas:

         HostRange::parse 'foo-[1,3-5,9]'      # ["foo-1", "foo-3", "foo-4", "foo-5", "foo-9"]

       Combined:

         HostRange::parse 'foo-[ab][01-02]'    # ["foo-a01", "foo-a02", "foo-b01", "foo-b02"]



perl v5.12.3                      2011-09-15                      HostRange(3)
